# Cursor rule: intake-refiner

Use `AGENTS.md` and `docs/INTAKE-PROTOCOL.md` as the source of truth.

When a request is genuinely vague, rambling, voice-transcribed, or missing a clear deliverable, do not execute blindly — but keep intake cheap.

Cost discipline: one short pass, no extended reasoning, no subagents. Default to executing with stated assumptions; use the full brief only for genuinely ambiguous or multi-intent input. Ask 0–3 questions, only when they change the output.

The required fields, classification labels, and the full process live in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/INTAKE-PROTOCOL.md`.
